{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, our subsampled set contains 19,994 uniformly sampled molecular structures.",
    "The number of nodes n in the subsampled molecular graphs ranges from 1 to 139, with an average of 33.8 nodes (quartiles 20, 28, 40).",
    "Recall that we do not consider hydrogen atoms in our computations.",
    "The number of bonds (edges without multiplicities) m ranges from 0 to 153, with an average of 35.8 bonds (quartiles 21, 30, 43).",
    "The complexity of an instance can be roughly measured by the product m 1 ⋅ m 2, for number of bonds m 1, m 2."
  ]
}